# concepts
## <DragDropContext>
- the background of all drags and drops happen.
- has 3 callback functions, onDragStart, onDrag...???, onDragEnd=> MUST
- you have to define your own ```onDragEnd```, what will happen when a draggable arrives.
- in my world time, the most basic version is to change order of timezone. => reorder function
```
reorder = (list, startIndex, endIndex) => {
  const result = Array.from(list);
  const [removed] = result.splice(startIndex, 1);
  result.splice(endIndex, 0, removed);

  return result;
};
```
- the DragEnd function has ```result``` parameter.
```
onDragEnd = (result) => {
    // dropped outside the list
    if (!result.destination) {
      return;
    }

    const items = this.reorder(
      this.state.items,
      result.source.index,
      result.destination.index
    );

    this.setState({
      items
    });
  }
```
- use ```<DragDropContext> to wrap your columns and give the function.
```
<DragDropContext
onDragEnd={this.onDragEnd}
>
...// columns
</DragDropContext>
```

## <Droppable>
- in the column.js, wrap the dnd area with <Droppable/>, and assign the id
```
<Droppable
  droppableId="droppable">
...//area
</Droppable>    
```
- Droppable should return a function???, and this function has ```provided``` parameter.     
***IMPORTANT ONE:*** 




